children.text: The plasterboard has not been stored in accordance with the manufacturer’s handling and storage requirements, which may cause damage to the plasterboard sheets.
The plasterboard sheet manufacturer’s installation manual requires that plasterboard be kept dry, must be stacked flat, properly supported on a flat surface or support members, see below;
The builder must immediately re-stack all of the plasterboard prior to any further damage, and remove/replace and plasterboard that has already been damaged as a result of the current storage method.
